cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper focuses on face recognition and uses deep learning techniques to address the challenge of large pose variations in unconstrained environments. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel deep 3D Morphable Model (3DMM) conditioned Face Frontalization Generative Adversarial Network (GAN), which involves both generative models and discriminative models, indicating that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of shape and appearance priors, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves 3D reconstruction, which may indicate that it belongs to cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
